---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="About the Downtown Lincoln Events project and its simple community-focused approach."
>
  <section class="page-section">
    <h1 class="page-section__title">About</h1>
    <p class="page-section__lede">
      Downtown Lincoln Events is meant to be a simple, fast, community-friendly place to browse
      what is happening around town.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="page-section">
    <div class="card-grid">
      <article class="card">
        <h2>The idea</h2>
        <p>
          Event management stays in one public calendar, while the website gives residents a more
          welcoming and readable way to explore upcoming plans.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <h2>The approach</h2>
        <p>
          The site will stay static and inexpensive to host. Astro will fetch the calendar feed at
          build time and generate pages from that data.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
